**Canvas Kit v14 components (prototypes):**
- **Layout**: `Box`, `Flex`, `Card`
- **Buttons**: `PrimaryButton`, `SecondaryButton`, `TertiaryButton`, `ToolbarIconButton`
- **Inputs**: `TextInput`, `InputGroup` (search / leading icon pattern), `FormSelect` (shared component for dropdowns), `Select` (compound component - advanced only), `FormField` + `FormField.Label` + `FormField.Input as={...}`, `Radio`, `Checkbox`
- **Display**: `CountBadge` (toolbar counts), `Table` (with `.Head`, `.Body`, `.Row`, `.Header`, `.Cell`)
- **Navigation**: `Tabs` (with `.List`, `.Item`, `.Panel`)
- **Text**: `Heading`, `BodyText`, `Text`
- **Icons**: `SystemIcon` (from `@workday/canvas-kit-react/icon`), Avatar
- **Popups**: `Modal`, `Popup`, `Toast`

**Select Component - IMPORTANT:**
Canvas Kit v14 `Select` is a **compound component** for advanced use cases:
- `Select.Input` - text input with typeahead
- `Select.List` - dropdown list container
- `Select.Item` - individual options
- `Select.Popper` - positioning wrapper

**For simple dropdowns** (filters, status selectors):
- Use `FormSelect` from `design/components/SharedFormControls.tsx`
- Implements native HTML `<select>` with FormField wrapper
- Proper for 90% of prototype filter/form use cases

**For complex autocomplete/search** (rare in prototypes):
- Use full Canvas Kit Select compound component pattern
- Consult Canvas Kit MCP for implementation details

