**Usage examples:**
- Interview stage badge: `blueberry100` bg + `blueberry600` text
- Completed step: `green500` dot + `blackPepper600` label
- Rejected status: `soap200` bg + `blackPepper600` text
- Metadata timestamp: `blackPepper500` color
- Clickable file name: `SANA_LINK_ACCENT` color

**Component Props Pattern:**
Canvas Kit components use:
- Margin props: `margin="m"`, `marginBottom="l"`, `marginTop="s"`
- Padding props: `padding="l"`, `paddingX="m"`, `paddingY="s"`
- Layout props: `flex="1"`, `minWidth={300}`, `gap="s"`

**CRITICAL Canvas Kit v11 Setup Requirements:**
⚠️ **ALWAYS verify these are in place BEFORE implementing:**

1. **Install Canvas Tokens Web** (REQUIRED in v11):
   ```bash
   npm install @workday/canvas-tokens-web
   ```

2. **Import CSS variables in main.tsx/index.tsx** (REQUIRED):
   ```tsx
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/base/_variables.css';
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/system/_variables.css';
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/brand/_variables.css';
   ```
   
   Without these imports, Canvas Kit components will have NO styling (no colors, spacing, borders, shadows, etc.)

3. **Import Canvas Kit fonts**:
   ```tsx
   import { fonts } from '@workday/canvas-kit-react-fonts';
   import { Global, css } from '@emotion/react';
   
   <Global styles={css(...fonts, { body: { fontFamily: '"Roboto", sans-serif' } })} />
   ```

**Component-Specific Implementation Requirements:**

**Tabs Component:**
- MUST set `initialTab` prop to show default tab
- MUST use `data-id` prop (NOT `name`, NOT `id`) on BOTH `Tabs.Item` AND `Tabs.Panel`
- The `data-id` values must match between Item and Panel
- Example:
  ```tsx
  <Tabs initialTab="overview">
    <Tabs.List marginBottom="l">
      <Tabs.Item data-id="overview">Overview</Tabs.Item>
      <Tabs.Item data-id="settings">Settings</Tabs.Item>
    </Tabs.List>
    <Tabs.Panel data-id="overview">
      <BodyText>Overview content</BodyText>
    </Tabs.Panel>
    <Tabs.Panel data-id="settings">
      <BodyText>Settings content</BodyText>
    </Tabs.Panel>
  </Tabs>
  ```

**Table Component:**
- v11 uses compound component pattern with `.Head`, `.Body`, `.Row`, `.Header`, `.Cell`
- NO LONGER use `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, `<td>` HTML elements
- Example:
  ```tsx
  <Table>
    <Table.Head>
      <Table.Row>
        <Table.Header>Column 1</Table.Header>
        <Table.Header>Column 2</Table.Header>
      </Table.Row>
    </Table.Head>
    <Table.Body>
      <Table.Row>
        <Table.Cell>Data 1</Table.Cell>
        <Table.Cell>Data 2</Table.Cell>
      </Table.Row>
    </Table.Body>
  </Table>
  ```

**TextInput Component:**
- Style props go directly on component (NOT via `inputProps`)
- Use `style={{}}` for custom styling
- Example:
  ```tsx
  <TextInput
    placeholder="Search..."
    value={value}
    onChange={(e) => setValue(e.target.value)}
    style={{ width: '100%', backgroundColor: colors.soap100 }}
  />
  ```

**Icon Components:**
- Use `SystemIcon` component (NOT old `Icon` component)
- Import icons from `@workday/canvas-system-icons-web`
- Common icons: `plusIcon`, `searchIcon`, `justifyIcon` (hamburger menu), `homeIcon`
- Example:
  ```tsx
  import { SystemIcon } from '@workday/canvas-kit-react/icon';
  import { searchIcon, justifyIcon } from '@workday/canvas-system-icons-web';
  
  <SystemIcon icon={searchIcon} size={16} color={colors.blackPepper400} />
  ```

**Button Components:**
- `ToolbarIconButton` for icon-only buttons in headers/toolbars
- Takes `icon` prop and `aria-label` (required for accessibility)
- Example:
  ```tsx
  import { ToolbarIconButton } from '@workday/canvas-kit-react/button';
  import { justifyIcon } from '@workday/canvas-system-icons-web';
  
  <ToolbarIconButton icon={justifyIcon} aria-label="Menu" />
  ```

